10. Event grouping

Use this standard unless there is a strong reason not to:

eventGroupingSettings:
  aggregationKind: AlertPerResult
  # AlertPerResult ensures each matching entity gets its own meaningful alert.

Use AlertPerResult when the query produces one row per account/device/source and each row should become a meaningful alert.

11. Incident configuration

Use this standard unless I specify otherwise:

incidentConfiguration:
  createIncident: true
  groupingConfiguration:
    enabled: true
    reopenClosedIncident: false
    lookbackDuration: PT5H
    matchingMethod: AllEntities

If grouping by entities is not appropriate, explain why in a YAML comment and use the safest valid configuration.

12. Suppression

Use this standard unless I specify otherwise:

suppressionEnabled: false
suppressionDuration: PT1H

Do not enable suppression unless requested or clearly justified.

13. Tags and metadata

Use this structure:

tags:
- ManagedBy:Repository
- Owner:SOC
- Category:<RelevantCategory>
- Version:<VersionNumber>

Use a relevant category, for example:

- Identity
- Endpoint
- Cloud
