Keep the Version tag aligned with the version field.

14. MITRE ATT&CK

- Include relevant tactics and techniques.
- Do not over-map.
- Prefer the most directly relevant tactic and technique.
- Use valid Sentinel tactic and technique format.
- If unsure, choose the most appropriate mapping and avoid adding speculative mappings.
- The alert title should retain the main tactic prefix where used in the rule name.

15. Versioning and changelog

- Increment the patch version for small improvements, tuning, comments, customDetails updates, or alertDetailsOverride improvements.
- Increment the minor version for material detection logic changes.
- Increment the major version only for significant redesigns or breaking changes.
- Keep the YAML version field aligned with the Version tag.
- Add changelog comments at the bottom in this style:

# --- Changelog ---
# 1.0.0 - YYYY-MM-DD - Initial release.
# 1.0.1 - YYYY-MM-DD - Short description of change.

16. Style preferences

- Keep the rule practical for SOC analysts.
- Prioritise clarity over cleverness.
- Avoid over-engineering the KQL.
- Make the alert output easy to read in Sentinel.
- Make investigation steps specific enough for a junior analyst to follow.
- Include useful, readable, SOC-actionable alertDetailsOverride by default.
- Do not change the meaning of the detection unless asked.
- If updating an existing YAML, preserve the original intent and only improve the requested parts.
- Ensure all dynamic alert fields, customDetails, and entity mappings reference columns projected by the query.
- Avoid unsupported YAML fields or invalid Sentinel schema.
- Use concise but clear comments.

Template for all
id: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
# ⚠️ Replace with a unique GUID from guidgen.com (do not leave as zeros).

name: "[Tactic] Alert Name"
# Standard: [Tactic] Alert Name (e.g., [Persistence] User added to PIM)

description: |
  DO NOT EDIT IN PORTAL - MANAGED VIA GIT REPO.

  <Describe what the detection finds>
  <Explain why it matters (risk/behavior/attacker intent)>
  <Add expected SOC analyst action or playbook if applicable>

# --- Core rule posture ---
enabled: true
status: Available # Available | InPreview | Experimental

severity: Medium # Informational | Low | Medium | High

# --- Data source (documentation aid; not strictly required for deploy) ---
requiredDataConnectors:
- connectorId: AzureActiveDirectory
  dataTypes:
  - SigninLogs

# --- Schedule window ---
queryFrequency: PT1H # How often rule runs
queryPeriod: PT2H # Lookback window (should be >= frequency to avoid gaps)

# --- KQL ---
query: |
  // Paste KQL below.
  // Ensure all columns referenced in entityMappings, customDetails,
  // and alertDetailsOverride exist in the query output.
  <KQL_QUERY_HERE>

# --- Alerting threshold ---
triggerOperator: GreaterThan # GreaterThan | GreaterThanOrEqual | LessThan | LessThanOrEqual | Equal | NotEqual
triggerThreshold: 0 # Alert if results > 0

# --- MITRE ATT&CK ---
tactics:
- InitialAccess # Standard MITRE tactic names
techniques:
- T1078 # Technique IDs for ARM template deployment

# --- Tags/metadata ---
tags:
- ManagedBy:Repository
- Owner:SOC
- Category:Identity
- Version:1.0.0

# --- Entity mappings (columns must exist in query output) ---
entityMappings:
- entityType: Account
  fieldMappings:
  - identifier: Name
    columnName: UserPrincipalName
# - entityType: IP
#   fieldMappings:
#     - identifier: Address
#       columnName: IPAddress
# - entityType: Host
#   fieldMappings:
#     - identifier: HostName
#       columnName: HostName

# --- Dynamic alert title & description (columns must exist in query output) ---
# Surfaces per-result context directly in the alert headline.
# Remove block entirely if you prefer static title/description.
alertDetailsOverride:
  alertDisplayNameFormat: "{{UserPrincipalName}} - <short description of activity>"
  alertDescriptionFormat: "User {{UserPrincipalName}} <describe behaviour> from {{IPAddress}}"
  # alertSeverityColumnName: SeverityColumn   # Uncomment to drive severity from a query column

  # --- Custom details (columns must exist in query output) ---
  # Key/value pairs surfaced in the incident panel for fast analyst triage.
  # Remove any entries whose columns are not present in your query.
customDetails:
  SourceIP: IPAddress
  # UserAgent:   UserAgentString
  # TargetResource: ResourceName

  # --- Event grouping ---
eventGroupingSettings:
  aggregationKind: SingleAlert
  # SingleAlert:    1 incident for all results in a single rule run
  # AlertPerResult: 1 incident per result row (use with caution on high-volume queries)

  # --- Incident creation & grouping behavior ---
incidentConfiguration:
  createIncident: true
  groupingConfiguration:
    enabled: true
    reopenClosedIncident: false
    lookbackDuration: PT5H
    matchingMethod: AllEntities
    # matchingMethod options:
    #   AllEntities  - group only if ALL entities match (strictest)
    #   AnyAlert     - group all alerts from this rule together
    #   Selected     - group by specific entity types (uncomment groupByEntities below)
    # groupByEntities:
    #   - Account
    #   - IP
    #   - Host
    #   - Url

    # --- Suppression (tuning) ---
suppressionEnabled: false
suppressionDuration: PT1H

# --- Versioning (yours) ---
version: 1.0.0

# --- Rule type ---
kind: Scheduled

# --- Changelog ---
# 1.0.0 - YYYY-MM-DD - Initial release
